00:04:15.757 --> 00:04:30.480 align:middle line:84%
She took the virus.

00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:32.690 align:middle line:90%
One of the soldiers
got away with the virus.

00:04:32.690 --> 00:04:39.656 align:middle line:90%
I want her on the run
with no place to turn.

00:04:39.656 --> 00:04:42.116 align:middle line:84%
She is a wily one.

00:04:42.116 --> 00:04:43.243 align:middle line:84%
Monitor all channels

00:04:43.243 --> 00:04:45.203 align:middle line:84%
and make sure she takes the fall for it.

00:04:45.203 --> 00:04:46.829 align:middle line:90%
- Understand?
- Yes, sir.

00:04:46.829 --> 00:04:49.123 align:middle line:90%
What you want us to do
with these assholes?

00:04:49.123 --> 00:04:52.293 align:middle line:84%
Clean it up. I don't care. No witnesses.

00:04:52.293 --> 00:04:55.046 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna get it back.

00:04:55.046 --> 00:05:45.180 align:middle line:84%
Who's gonna stop me?

00:05:45.180 --> 00:06:42.946 align:middle line:90%
- Where?
- Where?

00:06:42.946 --> 00:06:44.364 align:middle line:84%
Who the hell are you?

00:06:44.364 --> 00:06:59.254 align:middle line:90%
Ooh. I'm what you call
"an ice-cold can of whup-ass."

00:06:59.254 --> 00:07:01.047 align:middle line:84%
Who the hell are you?

00:07:01.047 --> 00:07:16.354 align:middle line:90%
I'm what you might call
"a champagne problem."

00:07:16.354 --> 00:07:42.172 align:middle line:84%
What you got, big man?

00:07:42.172 --> 00:07:48.428 align:middle line:84%
Really thought that would have broke.

00:07:48.428 --> 00:07:55.143 align:middle line:84%
Uh-uh.

00:07:55.143 --> 00:07:56.561 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna kill you!

00:07:56.561 --> 00:08:14.621 align:middle line:84%
You gonna die!

00:08:14.621 --> 00:08:16.539 align:middle line:84%
All right, all right. Oh, no, no.

00:08:16.539 --> 00:08:18.166 align:middle line:84%
That's my favorite jacket. Don't do that.

00:08:18.166 --> 00:08:20.960 align:middle line:90%
Hi, sweetheart.
Could you pass me that gun, please?

00:08:20.960 --> 00:08:23.922 align:middle line:84%
Thank you very much. Nice tats.

00:08:23.922 --> 00:08:25.381 align:middle line:90%
All right, ass-clown.
We're gonna play a little game.

00:08:25.381 --> 00:08:26.799 align:middle line:84%
It's called hangman.

00:08:26.799 --> 00:08:28.134 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna ask you some questions.

00:08:28.134 --> 00:08:31.429 align:middle line:84%
When you give me an answer I don't like...

00:08:31.429 --> 00:08:33.348 align:middle line:84%
Okay, you get the idea.

00:08:33.348 --> 00:08:34.724 align:middle line:84%
I've been tracking some dark web chatter

00:08:34.724 --> 00:08:35.808 align:middle line:84%
about a super virus

00:08:35.808 --> 00:08:37.769 align:middle line:84%
that's coming up on the auction block.

00:08:37.769 --> 00:08:39.187 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you tell me about it?

00:08:39.187 --> 00:08:41.064 align:middle line:84%
I swear, I don't know.

00:08:41.064 --> 00:08:45.026 align:middle line:84%
I don't like that answer.

00:08:45.026 --> 00:08:47.237 align:middle line:90%
A little bird told me
about a shadow outfit.

00:08:47.237 --> 00:08:49.656 align:middle line:84%
Black tech. Blood ops.

00:08:49.656 --> 00:08:52.158 align:middle line:84%
Real assholes. Like you.

00:08:52.158 --> 00:08:53.535 align:middle line:84%
They're called Eteon.

00:08:53.535 --> 00:08:55.328 align:middle line:90%
And you're gonna tell me
where to find them.

00:08:55.328 --> 00:08:56.412 align:middle line:84%
You're not gonna tell me

00:08:56.412 --> 00:08:58.081 align:middle line:84%
because I'm hanging you out of a window.

00:08:58.081 --> 00:08:59.499 align:middle line:84%
You're gonna tell me

00:08:59.499 --> 00:09:08.675 align:middle line:84%
because I'm the guy willing to drop you.

00:09:08.675 --> 00:09:10.885 align:middle line:84%
All right, bonus round.

00:09:10.885 --> 00:09:12.178 align:middle line:84%
Where's the virus?

00:09:12.178 --> 00:09:13.972 align:middle line:84%
No! No, wait!

00:09:13.972 --> 00:09:16.432 align:middle line:84%
Don't leave me out here! Please!

00:09:16.432 --> 00:09:23.147 align:middle line:84%
Don't leave me! Don't leave me!

00:09:23.147 --> 00:09:41.791 align:middle line:84%
What did he write?

00:09:41.791 --> 00:09:45.128 align:middle line:84%
"A, A, A." Excellent.

00:09:45.128 --> 00:09:47.505 align:middle line:90%
Oh, by the way,
your Old Man and the Sea report

00:09:47.505 --> 00:09:48.590 align:middle line:84%
from last week?

00:09:48.590 --> 00:09:50.341 align:middle line:84%
You did so good, it was awesome.

00:09:50.341 --> 00:09:52.010 align:middle line:90%
- Thanks, Daddy.
- Give me some. Yes. Yeah.

00:09:52.010 --> 00:09:53.595 align:middle line:84%
What's that?

00:09:53.595 --> 00:09:57.640 align:middle line:84%
Um, it's a social studies assignment.

00:09:57.640 --> 00:09:59.559 align:middle line:84%
It's a family tree.

00:09:59.559 --> 00:10:01.853 align:middle line:84%
It's just a sketch.

00:10:01.853 --> 00:10:03.396 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah.

00:10:03.396 --> 00:10:06.941 align:middle line:90%
That's our family tree right there.
It's, uh...

00:10:06.941 --> 00:10:12.822 align:middle line:84%
It's super easy to read and very clear.

00:10:12.822 --> 00:10:14.490 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.

00:10:14.490 --> 00:10:19.037 align:middle line:84%
But I was going to use this.

00:10:19.037 --> 00:10:22.248 align:middle line:84%
I found it in a garage drawer.

00:10:22.248 --> 00:10:25.335 align:middle line:84%
That's you, isn't it?

00:10:25.335 --> 00:10:27.545 align:middle line:84%
Who's Jonah?

00:10:27.545 --> 00:10:31.341 align:middle line:84%
Is that your brother?

00:10:31.341 --> 00:10:33.134 align:middle line:84%
Yup. That's my brother.

00:10:33.134 --> 00:10:36.346 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you ever talk about Samoa?

00:10:36.346 --> 00:10:38.181 align:middle line:84%
Did something happen?

00:10:38.181 --> 00:10:40.767 align:middle line:84%
In life, things happen.

00:10:40.767 --> 00:10:45.939 align:middle line:84%
You may not want them to, but they do.

00:10:45.939 --> 00:10:49.651 align:middle line:84%
You just gotta do your best...

00:10:49.651 --> 00:10:51.027 align:middle line:84%
and move on.

00:10:51.027 --> 00:10:54.280 align:middle line:90%
And the fact of the matter is
I'm your family.

00:10:54.280 --> 00:10:56.908 align:middle line:84%
I'm your people. Me.

00:10:56.908 --> 00:11:00.161 align:middle line:90%
- And you're a whole lot.
- Oh, I am a whole lot.

00:11:00.161 --> 00:11:03.706 align:middle line:84%
Look at this. Perfect timing.

00:11:03.706 --> 00:11:05.500 align:middle line:84%
Oh, no, this is the mini.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:07.877 align:middle line:90%
- Yup.
- Thank you so much.

00:11:07.877 --> 00:11:11.172 align:middle line:90%
- Cheat day?
- Cheat day. Yeah.

00:11:11.172 --> 00:11:15.969 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much.

00:11:15.969 --> 00:11:17.470 align:middle line:84%
Is that really necessary?

00:11:17.470 --> 00:11:19.264 align:middle line:84%
Come on! She's 71 years old.

00:11:19.264 --> 00:11:20.348 align:middle line:84%
What's the matter with you lot?

00:11:20.348 --> 00:11:23.434 align:middle line:90%
Sir, the prisoner will
only be allowed more leniency

00:11:23.434 --> 00:11:25.812 align:middle line:90%
when she proves
to be less of a security risk.

00:11:25.812 --> 00:11:27.438 align:middle line:84%
If someone leaves a back door open,

00:11:27.438 --> 00:11:29.065 align:middle line:84%
it's a bit daft not to try and use it.

00:11:29.065 --> 00:11:31.651 align:middle line:90%
What's daft is paying
one of the screws to leave it open

00:11:31.651 --> 00:11:33.403 align:middle line:90%
but not paying them enough
to keep their mouth shut.

00:11:33.403 --> 00:11:35.697 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, well, my point still stands.

00:11:35.697 --> 00:11:37.907 align:middle line:90%
If you can't break out
of a shitty prison like this,

00:11:37.907 --> 00:11:39.450 align:middle line:84%
then you're seriously slipping, Mum.

00:11:39.450 --> 00:11:40.952 align:middle line:84%
You cheeky bugger.

00:11:40.952 --> 00:11:43.288 align:middle line:90%
Speaking of breaking out,
where's my birthday cake?

00:11:43.288 --> 00:11:45.874 align:middle line:90%
The one with the file in it?
They're baking it.

00:11:45.874 --> 00:11:47.125 align:middle line:84%
Who wants a bloody file?

00:11:47.125 --> 00:11:48.793 align:middle line:84%
What I want is a nice little bit of C-4.

00:11:48.793 --> 00:11:50.962 align:middle line:84%
Listen, if you want out of here,

00:11:50.962 --> 00:11:53.381 align:middle line:84%
just say the word. I'll handle it.

00:11:53.381 --> 00:11:55.300 align:middle line:90%
Oh, Decks, I'm just having
a bit of fun really.

00:11:55.300 --> 00:11:57.302 align:middle line:84%
Being banged up doesn't bother me.

00:11:57.302 --> 00:11:59.012 align:middle line:84%
I quite enjoy the peace and quiet.

00:11:59.012 --> 00:12:00.513 align:middle line:84%
You know, nice walk,

00:12:00.513 --> 00:12:02.682 align:middle line:84%
bit of reading, loads of sudoku.

00:12:02.682 --> 00:12:05.435 align:middle line:84%
It's like being retired. Love it.

00:12:05.435 --> 00:12:08.938 align:middle line:90%
Now listen, have you spoken
with your sister?

00:12:08.938 --> 00:12:10.356 align:middle line:84%
You know I haven't, Mum.

00:12:10.356 --> 00:12:11.941 align:middle line:90%
- Give me your hand.
- There she goes.

00:12:11.941 --> 00:12:15.028 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you and your sister,
you used to be inseparable.

00:12:15.028 --> 00:12:17.447 align:middle line:90%
What happened, Decks?
What happened between you?

00:12:17.447 --> 00:12:19.365 align:middle line:84%
I remember you, Owen, and Hattie

00:12:19.365 --> 00:12:21.409 align:middle line:84%
playing out in the backyard.

00:12:21.409 --> 00:12:23.703 align:middle line:84%
Your little games, your little grifts.

00:12:23.703 --> 00:12:25.330 align:middle line:84%
Robbing banks.

00:12:25.330 --> 00:12:27.457 align:middle line:90%
You used to give
your little scams code names.

00:12:27.457 --> 00:12:28.541 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember?

00:12:28.541 --> 00:12:32.045 align:middle line:90%
- Oh, what was that one? Um...
- The "Keith Moon."

00:12:32.045 --> 00:12:33.588 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's right.

00:12:33.588 --> 00:12:35.048 align:middle line:90%
It was called the "Keith Moon"
because it...

00:12:35.048 --> 00:12:37.217 align:middle line:90%
It involved
lots of explosive percussion

00:12:37.217 --> 00:12:48.269 align:middle line:84%
and permanent ear damage.

00:12:48.269 --> 00:12:49.354 align:middle line:84%
That's my boy.

00:12:49.354 --> 00:12:51.523 align:middle line:84%
No wonder we left the family business.

00:12:51.523 --> 00:12:52.899 align:middle line:84%
She loves you, you know?

00:12:52.899 --> 00:12:55.777 align:middle line:90%
All you gotta do
is pick up the phone, Decks.

00:12:55.777 --> 00:12:59.322 align:middle line:84%
Look at me. You're her big brother.

00:12:59.322 --> 00:13:00.573 align:middle line:84%
She looks up to you.

00:13:00.573 --> 00:13:05.245 align:middle line:84%
Used to.

00:13:05.245 --> 00:13:09.958 align:middle line:90%
Well, one day, I just hope
that I walk through that door

00:13:09.958 --> 00:13:12.293 align:middle line:84%
and I see the two of you sitting there.

00:13:12.293 --> 00:13:14.045 align:middle line:84%
How many years you got left?

00:13:14.045 --> 00:13:15.630 align:middle line:84%
Two, with good behavior.

00:13:15.630 --> 00:13:20.051 align:middle line:90%
- So how many, really?
- Four.

00:13:20.051 --> 00:13:22.512 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know what they say.

00:13:22.512 --> 00:13:24.681 align:middle line:84%
"Never say 'never.'"

00:13:24.681 --> 00:13:26.474 align:middle line:84%
Time's up.

00:13:26.474 --> 00:13:28.017 align:middle line:84%
You behave yourself.

00:13:28.017 --> 00:13:29.853 align:middle line:84%
Will do. Love you, darling.

00:13:29.853 --> 00:13:45.368 align:middle line:84%
Love you too.

00:13:45.368 --> 00:13:48.872 align:middle line:90%
- All right.
- Lucas Rebecca Hobbs.

00:13:48.872 --> 00:13:51.332 align:middle line:84%
I haven't seen you in forever.

00:13:51.332 --> 00:13:52.417 align:middle line:84%
"Rebecca"?

00:13:52.417 --> 00:13:54.919 align:middle line:84%
Do you even age? How long's it been?

00:13:54.919 --> 00:13:56.171 align:middle line:90%
- Six months.
- Time flies.

00:13:56.171 --> 00:13:57.255 align:middle line:84%
When we're apart.

00:13:57.255 --> 00:13:59.007 align:middle line:84%
What is your skin care regimen?

00:13:59.007 --> 00:14:01.926 align:middle line:90%
Because you look
like a young Shirley Temple.

00:14:01.926 --> 00:14:03.052 align:middle line:84%
Go, go, go, go, go.

00:14:03.052 --> 00:14:04.345 align:middle line:84%
Daddy, who is this guy?

00:14:04.345 --> 00:14:08.141 align:middle line:84%
Well, this guy is, uh, Locke.

00:14:08.141 --> 00:14:10.268 align:middle line:84%
And he works for the CIA.

00:14:10.268 --> 00:14:11.394 align:middle line:84%
Your dad and I are old friends.

00:14:11.394 --> 00:14:14.230 align:middle line:90%
- We're not old friends.
- Actually, we're, um...

00:14:14.230 --> 00:14:15.648 align:middle line:84%
We're best friends. Here's the half heart.

00:14:15.648 --> 00:14:17.025 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what that is.

00:14:17.025 --> 00:14:18.109 align:middle line:84%
We got some ink together as well.

00:14:18.109 --> 00:14:19.194 align:middle line:84%
We did not get ink together.

00:14:19.194 --> 00:14:20.570 align:middle line:90%
- Oh, we didn't?
- No, we did not.

00:14:20.570 --> 00:14:22.155 align:middle line:90%
- Huh. Interesting.
- We never got ink together.

00:14:22.155 --> 00:14:23.239 align:middle line:84%
Well, I seem to remember

00:14:23.239 --> 00:14:24.824 align:middle line:84%
getting a little something like this

00:14:24.824 --> 00:14:26.868 align:middle line:84%
at one point on my body.

00:14:26.868 --> 00:14:27.952 align:middle line:90%
- Jesus.
- Christ,

00:14:27.952 --> 00:14:29.078 align:middle line:84%
I miss our playful banter.

00:14:29.078 --> 00:14:30.663 align:middle line:90%
You have one minute
to tell me what you want

00:14:30.663 --> 00:14:32.040 align:middle line:84%
before I knock one of your lungs loose.

00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:33.958 align:middle line:84%
You and I are after the same thing.

00:14:33.958 --> 00:14:36.336 align:middle line:84%
Say hello to the CT-17 virus.

00:14:36.336 --> 00:14:39.255 align:middle line:90%
It's a programmable bioweapon
of biblical proportions.

00:14:39.255 --> 00:14:41.799 align:middle line:84%
Affectionately code-named "the Snowflake."

00:14:41.799 --> 00:14:43.051 align:middle line:84%
What does the Snowflake do?

00:14:43.051 --> 00:14:44.135 align:middle line:84%
Oh, nothing much.

00:14:44.135 --> 00:14:45.803 align:middle line:84%
Just, uh, liquefies your internal organs.

00:14:45.803 --> 00:14:48.765 align:middle line:90%
Basically turns your body
into a giant bag of hot soup.

00:14:48.765 --> 00:14:50.016 align:middle line:84%
She is nine.

00:14:50.016 --> 00:14:51.434 align:middle line:90%
- Seen worse.
- Where?

00:14:51.434 --> 00:14:52.852 align:middle line:84%
Game of Thrones. Janet's house.

00:14:52.852 --> 00:14:53.937 align:middle line:84%
I've never heard of it.

00:14:53.937 --> 00:14:55.021 align:middle line:84%
A Lannister always pays his debts.

00:14:55.021 --> 00:14:56.689 align:middle line:84%
You're never going over there again.

00:14:56.689 --> 00:14:58.775 align:middle line:90%
But there's a new
wrinkle in the case, Rebecca.

00:14:58.775 --> 00:15:03.029 align:middle line:90%
The specifics...
are all in the brief.

00:15:03.029 --> 00:15:04.489 align:middle line:84%
There you go.

00:15:04.489 --> 00:15:06.950 align:middle line:90%
- She's ready, Becca.
- She's nine. She's nine!

00:15:06.950 --> 00:15:09.744 align:middle line:90%
This is the only unit of CT-17
in existence,

00:15:09.744 --> 00:15:12.247 align:middle line:84%
and this Snowflake is now in the hands of

00:15:12.247 --> 00:15:14.415 align:middle line:84%
a rogue MI6 operative in London.

00:15:14.415 --> 00:15:17.669 align:middle line:84%
Dad, are all spies that pretty?

00:15:17.669 --> 00:15:19.838 align:middle line:84%
No. She is unusually attractive.

00:15:19.838 --> 00:15:21.047 align:middle line:84%
And deadly.

00:15:21.047 --> 00:15:22.841 align:middle line:84%
Last night she was part of an MI6 team

00:15:22.841 --> 00:15:24.300 align:middle line:84%
tasked with securing the virus.

00:15:24.300 --> 00:15:26.970 align:middle line:90%
She then proceeded to kill
her entire black ops squad.

00:15:26.970 --> 00:15:30.515 align:middle line:90%
She stabbed one guy
in the chest using a brick.

00:15:30.515 --> 00:15:32.100 align:middle line:84%
Do you know how hard that is?

00:15:32.100 --> 00:15:33.893 align:middle line:84%
To stab someone using a brick?

00:15:33.893 --> 00:15:35.061 align:middle line:90%
- Get to the point.
- The point is

00:15:35.061 --> 00:15:36.145 align:middle line:84%
there's no sharp edge.

00:15:36.145 --> 00:15:37.355 align:middle line:84%
How did she get an entire brick

00:15:37.355 --> 00:15:38.815 align:middle line:84%
into another person's chest?

00:15:38.815 --> 00:15:40.400 align:middle line:84%
She either had to be really strong

00:15:40.400 --> 00:15:41.776 align:middle line:90%
or the other person
had to have been, like,

