00:41:45.381 --> 00:41:47.133 align:middle line:84%
and so you're absolutely useless to me.

00:41:47.133 --> 00:41:48.468 align:middle line:84%
So I'm gonna go find the man

00:41:48.468 --> 00:41:50.220 align:middle line:90%
who can help me get this thing
out of my system.

00:41:50.220 --> 00:41:54.349 align:middle line:90%
- See ya.
- You mean this man?

00:41:54.349 --> 00:41:56.184 align:middle line:84%
I was tracking him before the attack.

00:41:56.184 --> 00:41:58.353 align:middle line:90%
He's hard to find but I think
I got a hell of a lead.

00:41:58.353 --> 00:41:59.646 align:middle line:84%
Russian newspaper.

00:41:59.646 --> 00:42:01.231 align:middle line:84%
Not just any old paper.

00:42:01.231 --> 00:42:05.360 align:middle line:90%
There's only one place
in London that sells that.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:08.154 align:middle line:84%
Thank you. See you tomorrow.

00:42:08.154 --> 00:42:19.082 align:middle line:84%
That's a bit optimistic.

00:42:19.082 --> 00:42:25.797 align:middle line:84%
Call the director.

00:42:25.797 --> 00:42:29.175 align:middle line:84%
Well, well, Deckard Shaw.

00:42:29.175 --> 00:42:31.553 align:middle line:84%
How complicated for you.

00:42:31.553 --> 00:42:33.012 align:middle line:84%
Not really.

00:42:33.012 --> 00:42:36.516 align:middle line:84%
He's also working with DSS, Luke Hobbs.

00:42:36.516 --> 00:42:39.769 align:middle line:84%
Hobbs. We have a history.

00:42:39.769 --> 00:42:41.396 align:middle line:84%
They're formidable.

00:42:41.396 --> 00:42:42.730 align:middle line:84%
Small fry.

00:42:42.730 --> 00:42:44.315 align:middle line:84%
I'll eliminate the two of them.

00:42:44.315 --> 00:42:45.775 align:middle line:84%
Get the asset back ASAP.

00:42:45.775 --> 00:42:47.360 align:middle line:84%
You get the girl,

00:42:47.360 --> 00:42:48.987 align:middle line:84%
extract the virus

00:42:48.987 --> 00:42:51.447 align:middle line:84%
and reprogram it for phase one.

00:42:51.447 --> 00:42:54.200 align:middle line:84%
We use that weapon to eliminate the weak

00:42:54.200 --> 00:42:57.287 align:middle line:84%
and anyone who would get in our way.

00:42:57.287 --> 00:42:59.330 align:middle line:90%
We're building
the perfect system, Brixton.

00:42:59.330 --> 00:43:02.876 align:middle line:90%
Hobbs and Shaw can be
considerable assets for Eteon.

00:43:02.876 --> 00:43:04.294 align:middle line:84%
Turn them.

00:43:04.294 --> 00:43:05.962 align:middle line:84%
"Turn 'em"?

00:43:05.962 --> 00:43:08.089 align:middle line:84%
Sorry, I don't follow.

00:43:08.089 --> 00:43:09.757 align:middle line:84%
I want them turned.

00:43:09.757 --> 00:43:11.634 align:middle line:84%
I want them working for the cause.

00:43:11.634 --> 00:43:13.386 align:middle line:84%
Understood?

00:43:13.386 --> 00:43:15.263 align:middle line:84%
They can't be turned.

00:43:15.263 --> 00:43:17.473 align:middle line:84%
What makes you so certain?

00:43:17.473 --> 00:43:19.517 align:middle line:90%
The last time we asked,
I got shot in the face.

00:43:19.517 --> 00:43:22.020 align:middle line:84%
That makes me very certain.

00:43:22.020 --> 00:43:24.981 align:middle line:90%
So, I suggest
that we take another approach.

00:43:24.981 --> 00:43:26.065 align:middle line:84%
Which is why...

00:43:26.065 --> 00:43:27.483 align:middle line:84%
I'm not asking, Brixton.

00:43:27.483 --> 00:43:29.777 align:middle line:84%
You show them the consequences of refusal.

00:43:29.777 --> 00:43:32.989 align:middle line:84%
Or perhaps I'll show them to you.

00:43:32.989 --> 00:43:34.699 align:middle line:84%
Is that a threat?

00:43:34.699 --> 00:43:36.743 align:middle line:90%
I'd remember
who you're relying on

00:43:36.743 --> 00:43:39.746 align:middle line:84%
for your survival.

00:43:39.746 --> 00:43:45.919 align:middle line:84%
All for the cause.

00:43:45.919 --> 00:43:47.545 align:middle line:90%
Look, honey, I have to talk
to you about something.

00:43:47.545 --> 00:43:48.713 align:middle line:84%
It's very important right now.

00:43:48.713 --> 00:43:49.964 align:middle line:84%
Remember how we spoke about

00:43:49.964 --> 00:43:51.341 align:middle line:84%
what would happen if things went sideways?

00:43:51.341 --> 00:43:54.719 align:middle line:90%
We called it a "code red."
Well, it's happening.

00:43:54.719 --> 00:43:56.262 align:middle line:84%
Is there anything I can do?

00:43:56.262 --> 00:43:58.765 align:middle line:90%
You need to stay home.
You're gonna be safe there.

00:43:58.765 --> 00:44:00.558 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, we've got the CIA

00:44:00.558 --> 00:44:02.977 align:middle line:84%
listening in on this call right now.

00:44:02.977 --> 00:44:04.729 align:middle line:84%
Watch this. Hi, Locke.

00:44:04.729 --> 00:44:06.231 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's safe, everybody's great.

00:44:06.231 --> 00:44:08.483 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually at, uh, our old diner here.

00:44:08.483 --> 00:44:12.695 align:middle line:90%
It's super weird being here
without you guys.

00:44:12.695 --> 00:44:15.240 align:middle line:84%
Think it's closed.

00:44:15.240 --> 00:44:17.242 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, brother.

00:44:17.242 --> 00:44:18.785 align:middle line:84%
Honey, I've already talked to Aunt Lisa.

00:44:18.785 --> 00:44:20.036 align:middle line:84%
She knows exactly what to do.

00:44:20.036 --> 00:44:22.664 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna be home as soon as I can.

00:44:22.664 --> 00:44:26.417 align:middle line:90%
- Love you.
- I love you back.

00:44:26.417 --> 00:44:29.462 align:middle line:84%
Goodbye.

00:44:29.462 --> 00:44:32.841 align:middle line:84%
Luke Hobbs and Deckard Shaw.

00:44:32.841 --> 00:44:35.260 align:middle line:84%
While Hobbs is an agent in the American...

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:38.596 align:middle line:84%
Tell us everything you know about this.

00:44:38.596 --> 00:44:40.974 align:middle line:84%
My God.

00:44:40.974 --> 00:44:43.142 align:middle line:90%
- When were you exposed?
- About 30 hours ago.

00:44:43.142 --> 00:44:45.645 align:middle line:90%
Then the capsules containing
the virus are still intact.

00:44:45.645 --> 00:44:46.980 align:middle line:84%
So we need to neutralize it.

00:44:46.980 --> 00:44:48.314 align:middle line:84%
No, it is not that easy.

00:44:48.314 --> 00:44:50.775 align:middle line:84%
It's not programmed to any DNA sequence.

00:44:50.775 --> 00:44:52.110 align:middle line:84%
It's fatal to everyone.

00:44:52.110 --> 00:44:54.070 align:middle line:84%
In 42 hours, the capsules will dissolve,

00:44:54.070 --> 00:44:55.154 align:middle line:84%
and she will be infected.

00:44:55.154 --> 00:44:57.365 align:middle line:84%
Then the virus will go airborne.

00:44:57.365 --> 00:45:00.618 align:middle line:90%
We are talking global
contamination within a week.

00:45:00.618 --> 00:45:02.537 align:middle line:90%
Why in the hell would you
create something like that?

00:45:02.537 --> 00:45:04.080 align:middle line:84%
Because I thought I was one of them.

00:45:04.080 --> 00:45:05.164 align:middle line:84%
Eteon.

00:45:05.164 --> 00:45:06.249 align:middle line:84%
They told me they wanted to

00:45:06.249 --> 00:45:07.584 align:middle line:84%
save the world through science.

00:45:07.584 --> 00:45:09.085 align:middle line:84%
I believed in their cause.

00:45:09.085 --> 00:45:12.547 align:middle line:90%
I developed the Snowflake
to be a carrier for vaccines,

00:45:12.547 --> 00:45:14.299 align:middle line:84%
a panacea for the whole world.

00:45:14.299 --> 00:45:17.802 align:middle line:90%
But they redeveloped it into
a programmable apocalypse.

00:45:17.802 --> 00:45:19.429 align:middle line:84%
To attack the weakest of us.

00:45:19.429 --> 00:45:22.348 align:middle line:90%
Those not worthy of Eteon's
vision of the future.

00:45:22.348 --> 00:45:24.475 align:middle line:90%
For a scientist,
you seem incredibly stupid.

00:45:24.475 --> 00:45:26.436 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm a two-times Nobel Prize winner,

00:45:26.436 --> 00:45:27.687 align:middle line:84%
but who's counting?

00:45:27.687 --> 00:45:30.064 align:middle line:90%
All right, you said
the virus is programmable.

00:45:30.064 --> 00:45:31.774 align:middle line:84%
So... reprogram it.

00:45:31.774 --> 00:45:33.818 align:middle line:84%
I can't reprogram it in a host.

00:45:33.818 --> 00:45:35.361 align:middle line:90%
Just tell us how to get
this thing out from me.

00:45:35.361 --> 00:45:37.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, there are two options.

00:45:37.530 --> 00:45:38.990 align:middle line:84%
And the first is easy.

00:45:38.990 --> 00:45:40.283 align:middle line:90%
- Go.
- Finally.

00:45:40.283 --> 00:45:41.868 align:middle line:90%
- You kill her.
- Excuse me?

00:45:41.868 --> 00:45:43.119 align:middle line:84%
Oh, and burn the body, of course.

00:45:43.119 --> 00:45:44.454 align:middle line:90%
- Of course.
- Of course.

00:45:44.454 --> 00:45:45.830 align:middle line:84%
No, I mean really burn it.

00:45:45.830 --> 00:45:47.040 align:middle line:90%
- Really burn it.
- To ash.

00:45:47.040 --> 00:45:48.750 align:middle line:90%
- To ash?
- Beyond all recognition.

00:45:48.750 --> 00:45:51.503 align:middle line:90%
Let's assume that that's not an option,
shall we, genius?

00:45:51.503 --> 00:45:53.213 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it doesn't work for us.
Option number two.

00:45:53.213 --> 00:45:55.048 align:middle line:90%
There is a machine
that could preserve her life

00:45:55.048 --> 00:45:56.132 align:middle line:84%
and extract the virus.

00:45:56.132 --> 00:45:57.509 align:middle line:84%
That should've been option number one.

00:45:57.509 --> 00:45:59.177 align:middle line:84%
Because it's impossible to get to.

00:45:59.177 --> 00:46:01.554 align:middle line:90%
We'll decide what's impossible.
Where is it?

00:46:01.554 --> 00:46:03.181 align:middle line:84%
It's in the Eteon laboratory

00:46:03.181 --> 00:46:04.516 align:middle line:84%
where the Snowflake was developed.

00:46:04.516 --> 00:46:07.477 align:middle line:90%
A secret dark-tech complex
fortified by an army

00:46:07.477 --> 00:46:10.188 align:middle line:90%
in the most godforsaken
part of the planet.

00:46:10.188 --> 00:46:12.357 align:middle line:90%
But if you go there,
all three of you will die.

00:46:12.357 --> 00:46:13.858 align:middle line:84%
So basically what you're saying is

00:46:13.858 --> 00:46:17.362 align:middle line:84%
she dies no matter what.

00:46:17.362 --> 00:46:20.615 align:middle line:84%
Well, who needs a drink?

00:46:20.615 --> 00:46:39.968 align:middle line:84%
I know just the place.

00:46:39.968 --> 00:46:42.804 align:middle line:84%
Wow, look at all these.

00:46:42.804 --> 00:46:44.764 align:middle line:84%
Somebody's overcompensating.

00:46:44.764 --> 00:46:48.893 align:middle line:84%
If anything, I'm under-compensating.

00:46:48.893 --> 00:46:53.565 align:middle line:90%
And a teeny-tiny one.
Just your size.

00:46:53.565 --> 00:46:56.359 align:middle line:84%
Used it for a job over in Italy.

00:46:56.359 --> 00:46:59.362 align:middle line:90%
Shame we didn't need
a weightlifting bus driver.

00:46:59.362 --> 00:47:09.873 align:middle line:84%
Would've given you a call.

00:47:09.873 --> 00:47:11.749 align:middle line:84%
Drink?

00:47:11.749 --> 00:47:29.976 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I'll take a little one.

00:47:29.976 --> 00:47:32.145 align:middle line:90%
I'll write to someone in Moscow.
An old friend.

00:47:32.145 --> 00:47:34.063 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, we have a long history.

00:47:34.063 --> 00:47:36.357 align:middle line:90%
She and her crew are paying
a visit to some locals.

00:47:36.357 --> 00:47:38.151 align:middle line:84%
Particular Russian criminal element.

00:47:38.151 --> 00:47:39.694 align:middle line:84%
They have things that we're gonna need.

00:47:39.694 --> 00:47:40.945 align:middle line:84%
Considering your history with friends,

00:47:40.945 --> 00:47:42.405 align:middle line:90%
how many bullets you put
in this one's head?

00:47:42.405 --> 00:47:43.698 align:middle line:84%
They can set us up with gear,

00:47:43.698 --> 00:47:44.949 align:middle line:84%
and I don't hear any other ideas.

00:47:44.949 --> 00:47:46.826 align:middle line:90%
You know as well as I do
getting out of this country

00:47:46.826 --> 00:47:48.203 align:middle line:84%
is gonna be extremely difficult.

00:47:48.203 --> 00:47:49.996 align:middle line:84%
We have every major intelligence agency

00:47:49.996 --> 00:47:51.247 align:middle line:84%
already hunting us down.

00:47:51.247 --> 00:47:53.082 align:middle line:90%
And there's the fact
that you disgraced MI6

00:47:53.082 --> 00:48:01.508 align:middle line:84%
when you betrayed your team.

00:48:01.508 --> 00:48:05.136 align:middle line:90%
Don't believe everything
they tell you, Hat.

00:48:05.136 --> 00:48:11.476 align:middle line:84%
Smile.

00:48:11.476 --> 00:48:13.353 align:middle line:90%
No, regular back channels
aren't gonna work this time.

00:48:13.353 --> 00:48:14.938 align:middle line:90%
We're gonna have to
do our best to blend in.

00:48:14.938 --> 00:48:16.314 align:middle line:84%
Hide in plain sight.

00:48:16.314 --> 00:48:18.191 align:middle line:84%
That's why we'll be flying commercial.

00:48:18.191 --> 00:48:19.317 align:middle line:84%
Commercial? We're gonna get spotted

00:48:19.317 --> 00:48:21.653 align:middle line:84%
too easy at...

00:48:21.653 --> 00:48:23.905 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry that pea-sized brain.
I handled it.

00:48:23.905 --> 00:48:25.949 align:middle line:90%
Cloned our cell phone signals
around the world.

00:48:25.949 --> 00:48:27.992 align:middle line:84%
Should buy us at least 48 hours.

00:48:27.992 --> 00:48:29.661 align:middle line:90%
We'll pick up new gear
when we get to Moscow.

00:48:29.661 --> 00:48:32.413 align:middle line:90%
Should get us past the
wandering eyes at the airport.

00:48:32.413 --> 00:48:36.209 align:middle line:90%
This is probably the only thing
that's gonna fit.

00:48:36.209 --> 00:48:37.877 align:middle line:84%
Fit what, a Smurf?

00:48:37.877 --> 00:48:39.504 align:middle line:84%
I think that's one of my old ones.

00:48:39.504 --> 00:48:40.672 align:middle line:84%
I apologize in advance

00:48:40.672 --> 00:48:43.591 align:middle line:84%
if it's a little loose around the balls.

00:48:43.591 --> 00:48:46.302 align:middle line:84%
Okay. What do we got, tough guy? Come on.

00:48:46.302 --> 00:48:47.679 align:middle line:84%
I've created new identities

00:48:47.679 --> 00:48:49.347 align:middle line:84%
and altered your biometric profiles

00:48:49.347 --> 00:48:50.849 align:middle line:84%
so the airport scanners don't recognize

00:48:50.849 --> 00:48:52.308 align:middle line:84%
your faces or your fingerprints.

00:48:52.308 --> 00:48:54.894 align:middle line:90%
You're Sarah Atkins.
You work in insurance.

00:48:54.894 --> 00:48:59.023 align:middle line:84%
Hello.

00:48:59.023 --> 00:49:01.192 align:middle line:90%
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

00:49:01.192 --> 00:49:02.819 align:middle line:84%
I'm Franz Gruber.

00:49:02.819 --> 00:49:06.614 align:middle line:90%
I'm a freelance architect,
avid mountain climber,

00:49:06.614 --> 00:49:10.952 align:middle line:84%
and a part-time ski instructor.

00:49:10.952 --> 00:49:12.036 align:middle line:84%
Thank you.

00:49:12.036 --> 00:49:17.500 align:middle line:84%
And you, you're Michael Oxmaul.

00:49:17.500 --> 00:49:23.965 align:middle line:84%
"Mike Oxmaul."

00:49:23.965 --> 00:49:26.801 align:middle line:84%
I go by Michael.

00:49:26.801 --> 00:49:27.886 align:middle line:90%
- Freeze!
- Stay right where you are!

00:49:27.886 --> 00:49:29.846 align:middle line:90%
- Stop, sir! Stop there!
- Stay there!

00:49:29.846 --> 00:49:31.431 align:middle line:84%
It's Mike. It's Mike Oxmaul.

00:49:31.431 --> 00:49:34.142 align:middle line:84%
It's not small. And my name's Michael.

00:49:34.142 --> 00:49:36.436 align:middle line:84%
They've stopped him for what, exactly?

00:49:36.436 --> 00:49:38.521 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it is,
it's gonna involve rubber gloves

00:49:38.521 --> 00:49:40.356 align:middle line:84%
and a body cavity search.

00:49:40.356 --> 00:49:44.736 align:middle line:84%
Let's go.

00:49:44.736 --> 00:49:54.078 align:middle line:84%
Hands on your head, Oxmaul.

00:49:54.078 --> 00:49:55.788 align:middle line:84%
Can't believe you did that.

00:49:55.788 --> 00:50:00.293 align:middle line:84%
He was gonna slow us down.

00:50:00.293 --> 00:50:03.213 align:middle line:84%
We can't pull this off. We both know it.

00:50:03.213 --> 00:50:04.756 align:middle line:90%
It's bad enough
I got this thing in my blood

00:50:04.756 --> 00:50:06.216 align:middle line:84%
that's gonna kill me and everyone else,

00:50:06.216 --> 00:50:08.426 align:middle line:90%
but were you seriously gonna
break this mysterious machine

00:50:08.426 --> 00:50:11.095 align:middle line:90%
out of some high-security
death virus complex

00:50:11.095 --> 00:50:12.805 align:middle line:84%
and magically get it to work?

00:50:12.805 --> 00:50:14.015 align:middle line:84%
Frankly, that sounds completely...

00:50:14.015 --> 00:50:17.352 align:middle line:84%
You still wear that silly thing?

00:50:17.352 --> 00:50:19.896 align:middle line:84%
Didn't know you still had that.

00:50:19.896 --> 00:50:22.607 align:middle line:84%
Put the pin back in.

00:50:22.607 --> 00:50:27.403 align:middle line:84%
You haven't changed.

00:50:27.403 --> 00:50:29.531 align:middle line:84%
Wish I could say the same about you.

00:50:29.531 --> 00:50:32.492 align:middle line:84%
Hey, you're gonna be okay.

00:50:32.492 --> 00:50:36.371 align:middle line:90%
We're gonna make this work.
It's what we do.

00:50:36.371 --> 00:50:40.083 align:middle line:84%
And what if we don't?

00:50:40.083 --> 00:50:41.501 align:middle line:84%
What if the only option is for you to...

00:50:41.501 --> 00:50:44.003 align:middle line:84%
It's not happening.

00:50:44.003 --> 00:50:50.927 align:middle line:84%
Hi, I'm here. I'm Michael.

00:50:50.927 --> 00:50:52.762 align:middle line:84%
Hi, yeah.

00:50:52.762 --> 00:50:56.182 align:middle line:84%
Hello. All right.

00:50:56.182 --> 00:51:00.478 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah, let's see. Where's my seat?

00:51:00.478 --> 00:51:04.190 align:middle line:84%
F-one, F-two...

00:51:04.190 --> 00:51:07.944 align:middle line:84%
F you.

00:51:07.944 --> 00:51:12.866 align:middle line:84%
Hey.

00:51:12.866 --> 00:51:15.368 align:middle line:84%
You are an asshole.

00:51:15.368 --> 00:51:16.661 align:middle line:84%
You were quicker than I thought.

00:51:16.661 --> 00:51:18.538 align:middle line:84%
Yup. Because I have a secret weapon.

00:51:18.538 --> 00:51:20.832 align:middle line:84%
People actually like me.

00:51:20.832 --> 00:51:21.916 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't understand that

00:51:21.916 --> 00:51:28.506 align:middle line:84%
because you don't have any friends.

00:51:28.506 --> 00:52:05.960 align:middle line:84%
I love your babushka.

00:52:05.960 --> 00:52:07.545 align:middle line:84%
Couldn't have booked an emergency row

00:52:07.545 --> 00:52:08.838 align:middle line:84%
for a little bit more legroom, huh?

00:52:08.838 --> 00:52:11.549 align:middle line:84%
Not everybody has hobbit legs like you.

00:52:11.549 --> 00:52:14.260 align:middle line:84%
Hey, look, in case you didn't realize,

00:52:14.260 --> 00:52:16.387 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't give a damn about your comfort.

00:52:16.387 --> 00:52:18.348 align:middle line:84%
So why don't you be a good elephant,

00:52:18.348 --> 00:52:20.475 align:middle line:84%
suck up another kilo of peanuts,

00:52:20.475 --> 00:52:22.519 align:middle line:84%
put your chair back and relax?

00:52:22.519 --> 00:52:24.229 align:middle line:90%
All right, listen,
don't ever tell me to relax, all right?

00:52:24.229 --> 00:52:25.313 align:middle line:84%
Don't tell me to do anything.

00:52:25.313 --> 00:52:26.731 align:middle line:84%
Any time you ever say anything,

00:52:26.731 --> 00:52:28.024 align:middle line:84%
it makes me want to take my boot

00:52:28.024 --> 00:52:29.317 align:middle line:84%
and shove it so far up your ass,

00:52:29.317 --> 00:52:31.110 align:middle line:90%
you're gonna be spitting out
shoelaces all week.

00:52:31.110 --> 00:52:33.821 align:middle line:84%
Hey, you know what the problem is?

00:52:33.821 --> 00:52:36.199 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you the problem. This job.

00:52:36.199 --> 00:52:38.785 align:middle line:84%
This job requires stealth.

00:52:38.785 --> 00:52:41.579 align:middle line:84%
And you... look at you.

00:52:41.579 --> 00:52:44.624 align:middle line:84%
I mean, granted, it's not your fault.

00:52:44.624 --> 00:52:46.084 align:middle line:84%
But you're too obvious.

00:52:46.084 --> 00:52:50.421 align:middle line:84%
You stick out. Like balls on a bulldog.

00:52:50.421 --> 00:52:53.132 align:middle line:84%
Dangling down in all the wrong places.

00:52:53.132 --> 00:52:57.095 align:middle line:84%
Seemingly harmless.

00:52:57.095 --> 00:52:58.179 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing you know,

00:52:58.179 --> 00:53:00.181 align:middle line:84%
they're trying to impregnate your sister.

00:53:00.181 --> 00:53:02.809 align:middle line:84%
What?

00:53:02.809 --> 00:53:06.229 align:middle line:90%
- Impregnate your sister?
- You heard.

00:53:06.229 --> 00:53:09.107 align:middle line:84%
Oh.

00:53:09.107 --> 00:53:10.400 align:middle line:84%
Now I get it.

00:53:10.400 --> 00:53:12.610 align:middle line:84%
You do? Good. I'm glad.

00:53:12.610 --> 00:53:14.279 align:middle line:90%
Mmm-hmm?
- Yeah, I'm glad.

00:53:14.279 --> 00:53:15.822 align:middle line:90%
- I'm very glad.
- You actually think that

00:53:15.822 --> 00:53:18.366 align:middle line:90%
I'm going through all this effort,
on this mission,

00:53:18.366 --> 00:53:21.578 align:middle line:90%
trying to save the world,
by the way, for a fourth time,

00:53:21.578 --> 00:53:23.204 align:middle line:84%
because I'm really good at it.

